M|What|tx|The Composer layers multiple elements (images, text, logos, vd) into a single composed visual. It is a ds canvas inside your workflow — not an AI generation md.
M|When|Use |
M|When|it|Ad creatives combining pd shot + hl + logo + CTA
M|When|it|sl posts w/ text overlay on generated background
M|When|it|Localized variants (same layout, different text)
M|When|it|A/B tst variants (same layout, swapped elements)
M|How |Conn|
M|How |tx|```
M|How |tx|[gn im (background)] → Composer (layer 1)
M|How |tx|[Upload im (logo)]         → Composer (layer 2)
M|How |[Tex|text overlay)
M|How |[Tex|text overlay)
M|How |tx|```
M|How |tx|Inside Composer, set layer positions, sizes, and z-ordering.
M|Powe|**Pa|Localization at scale**
M|Powe|tx|```
M|Powe|tx|[Base Composition] → Composer
M|Powe|tx|[Text Assistant (translate to FR/DE/ES...)] → Composer (text layer)
M|Powe|tx|```
M|Powe|tx|Run the ag N times w/ different language inputs — same layout, localized text.
M|Powe|**Pa|A/B hl testing**
M|Powe|tx|```
M|Powe|tx|[Split Text (from list of headlines)] → [List Selector (pick #N)] → Composer
M|Powe|tx|[Base im]                                                      → Composer
M|Powe|tx|```
M|Powe|tx|Each run picks a different hl variant.
M|Powe|**Pa|Static ad production**
M|Powe|tx|1. gn background/lifestyle im
M|Powe|tx|2. Upload pd shot → Remove Background
M|Powe|tx|3. gn hl text via Text Assistant
M|Powe|tx|4. Feed all three + br logo into Composer
M|Powe|5. O|cg-ready ad creative
M|Powe|tx|---
M|When|tx|Any workflow producing **public-facing creative cn** shd include br nodes.
M|Whic|tx|\| Scenario \| Add these br nodes \|
M|Whic|tx|\|---\|---\|
M|Whic|tx|\| im/vd generation needs to look on-br \| Visual References (upload style examples) \|
M|Whic|tx|\| AI md needs to know who the br is \| br Context \|
M|Whic|tx|\| Need to enforce specific creative rules \| br Guidelines \|
M|Whic|tx|\| Generating cp / captions / scripts \| br Voice \|
M|Whic|tx|\| Complex br w/ full doc \| br doc (PDF) \|
M|Wiri|Conn|
M|Wiri|tx|```
M|Wiri|tx|[Visual References] → GenerateImage
M|Wiri|tx|[br Guidelines] → GenerateImage
M|Wiri|tx|[br Context]    → TextAssistant
M|Wiri|tx|[br Voice]      → TextAssistant
M|Wiri|tx|```
M|Pro |tx|Upload real examples (Visual References, br Voice) rather than describing your br in text. The AI md learn faster from examples than from abstract descriptions.
M|Pro |tx|---
M|What|tx|Runs an LLM w/ a custom sy instruction. It's the most versatile node in Pletor.
M|When|tx|\| Task \| Use \|
M|When|tx|\|---\|---\|
M|When|tx|\| Mechanically join two text strings \| pm Concatenator (free, predictable) \|
M|When|tx|\| Enhance a vague us pm into a detailed generation pm \| Text Assistant \|
M|When|tx|\| Combine us pm + br context intelligently \| Text Assistant \|
M|When|tx|\| Translate or localize cp \| Text Assistant \|
M|When|tx|\| al an uploaded im or document \| Text Assistant \|
M|When|tx|\| gn multiple ad headlines \| Text Assistant \|
M|When|tx|\| Extract structured data from a doc \| Text Assistant \|
M|Syst|Alwa|
M|Syst|1. *|What the LLM is (e.g., "You are a creative director at a luxury fashion br")
M|Syst|2. *|Exactly what to do w/ the inputs
M|Syst|3. *|How to structure the output (important when output feeds another node)
M|Syst|4. *|br rules, word count limits, tone requirements
M|Syst|**Ex|**
M|Syst|tx|```
M|Syst|tx|You are an expert creative director specializing in luxury fashion photography.
M|Syst|Your|Take the us's input pm and rewrite it as a detailed, vivid im generation pm.
M|Syst|Rule|
M|Syst|it|Include lighting style, camera angle, background description, and mood
M|Syst|it|Maintain the br's editorial and sophisticated aesthetic
M|Syst|it|Keep output under 150 words
M|Syst|it|Output ONLY the enhanced pm, no preamble
M|Syst|tx|```
M|Syst|**Ex|**
M|Syst|tx|```
M|Syst|tx|You are a perf mk copywriter.
M|Syst|Your|gn 5 short ad headlines based on the pd description and br voice provided.
M|Syst|Form|Output as a numbered list, one hl per line.
M|Syst|Each|max 8 words, action-oriented, benefit-focused.
M|Syst|tx|```
M|Syst|tx|---
